🧩 Database Schema Design (MongoDB)
🍔 Food Model
{
  name String,
  description String,
  category String,  pizza, burger, drink
  price Number,
  image String,  Cloudinary URL
  available Boolean
}

👤 User Model
{
  name String,
  email String,
  password String,
  role { type String, default user }  admin or user
}

🛒 Order Model
{
  userId mongoose.Schema.Types.ObjectId,
  items [
    {
      foodId mongoose.Schema.Types.ObjectId,
      name String,
      quantity Number,
      price Number
    }
  ],
  totalPrice Number,
  status { type String, default Pending }  Preparing, Out for delivery, etc.
}

🚀 Step-by-Step Development Roadmap
🗓️ Phase 1 – Backend Setup (Days 1–3)

Initialize Node + Express project (npm init, install dependencies)

Setup MongoDB connection (Mongoose)

Create User, Food, and Order models

Create routes for

Auth (register, login)

Food (add-food, get-foods)

Orders (create-order, my-orders)

Implement JWT-based auth middleware

Test all routes in Postman

🗓️ Phase 2 – Frontend Setup (Days 4–6)

Setup React frontend (vite or CRA)

Install Axios, React Router DOM

Create pages Home, Cart, Login, Register

Display food items from backend API

Add “Add to Cart” and “Remove from Cart” logic

Create Context API for cart management

🗓️ Phase 3 – Authentication + Protected Routes (Days 7–9)

Implement user loginregister using JWT tokens

Store token in localStorage

Protect routes like cart and orders

Display user’s order history using token-based authentication

🗓️ Phase 4 – Admin Panel (Days 10–12)

Create Admin Dashboard (role-based access)

Add, edit, delete food items

View all orders

Update order status (dropdown or button)

🗓️ Phase 5 – Final Touch & Deployment (Days 13–15)

Add image upload (Multer + Cloudinary)

Optional Integrate Razorpay  Stripe for payments

Style frontend (Tailwind or your preferred CSS method)

Deploy backend (Render) & frontend (NetlifyVercel)

💡 Extra Features (for more challenge later)

🍟 Add combo meals (multiple items in one dish)

🔍 Add search and category filters

🔔 Use Socket.io for live order updates

🧾 Send order confirmation email

📊 Admin dashboard analytics with charts

